fields.name: High-Level Synthesis Flow
fields.description: This involves the creation of RTL designs from high-level programming languages such as C, C++, and SystemC.

fields.name: RTL Design Flow
fields.description: This involves the design of circuits using hardware description languages (HDLs) such as VHDL and Verilog.

fields.name: Functional Verification Flow
fields.description: This involves simulation, formal verification, and emulation to confirm that the design behaves as expected.

fields.name: Synthesis Flow
fields.description: This involves translating RTL designs into gate-level representations.

fields.name: Place and Route Flow
fields.description: This involves the process of arranging the layout of a chip, including the placement of cells and routing of interconnects.

fields.name: Timing Analysis Flow
fields.description: This involves checking that the design meets its timing requirements.

fields.name: Physical Verification Flow
fields.description: This involves checking for layout-versus-schematics (LVS), design rule checking (DRC), and electrical rule checking (ERC).

fields.name: System-on-Chip (SoC) Design Flow
fields.description: This involves the integration of multiple IP cores into a single chip.

fields.name: Multi-Chip Module (MCM) Design Flow
fields.description: This involves the integration of multiple dies into a single package.

fields.name: Printed Circuit Board (PCB) Design Flow
fields.description: This involves the design and layout of PCBs.

fields.name: Hard IP Core Flow
fields.description: This involves the design of cores that are delivered as a physical layout.

fields.name: Soft IP Core Flow
fields.description: This involves the design of cores that are delivered as RTL.
